WEBVTT



00:00:00.896 --> 00:00:05.888
Well hello friends and thank you for joining me in our daily reading from God's holy word

00:00:05.664 --> 00:00:08.672
Today we're reading Mark chapter 12,

00:00:08.608 --> 00:00:16.032
13-27. And in this lesson, we see Jesus demonstrate his wisdom and understanding. 13-27.

00:00:16.096 --> 00:00:19.360
As he refutes those who sought to trap him.

00:00:19.264 --> 00:00:20.640
And trip him up.

00:00:21.472 --> 00:00:23.712
Now before we read, let's pray.

00:00:24.192 --> 00:00:28.576
Our Father in Heaven, help us hear and believe Jesus.

00:00:28.672 --> 00:00:30.464
In his name, I ask it.

00:00:30.816 --> 00:00:32.096
Amen.

00:00:32.640 --> 00:00:33.568
Mark.

00:00:33.568 --> 00:00:36.480
Chapter 12, beginning in verse 13.

00:00:36.448 --> 00:00:41.824
And they sent to him some of the Pharisees and some of the Herodians.

00:00:41.632 --> 00:00:44.224
To trap him in his talk.

00:00:44.352 --> 00:00:51.392
And they came and said to him, Teacher, we know that you are true and do not care about anyone's opinion.

00:00:51.104 --> 00:00:56.640
For you are not swayed by appearances, but truly teach the way of God.

00:00:57.216 --> 00:00:58.624
Is it lawful?

00:00:58.464 --> 00:01:00.928
To pay taxes to Caesar,

00:01:00.704 --> 00:01:01.824
or not.

00:01:02.016 --> 00:01:03.488
Should we pay them?

00:01:03.552 --> 00:01:05.024
Or should we not?

00:01:05.664 --> 00:01:10.976
But knowing their hypocrisy, he said to them, Why put me to the test?

00:01:10.848 --> 00:01:13.728
Bring me a denarius and let me look at it.

00:01:13.984 --> 00:01:19.488
And they brought one, and he said to them, Whose likeness and inscription is this?

00:01:19.552 --> 00:01:22.016
They said to him, Caesar's.

00:01:22.080 --> 00:01:23.840
Jesus said to them,

00:01:23.968 --> 00:01:26.272
Render to Caesar.

00:01:26.016 --> 00:01:28.032
The things that are Caesar's.

00:01:27.904 --> 00:01:29.376
and to God,

00:01:29.248 --> 00:01:31.552
The things that are God's.

00:01:31.872 --> 00:01:33.824
And they marvelled at him.

00:01:34.496 --> 00:01:42.656
And sadducees came to him who say that there is no resurrection, and they asked him a question, saying, Teacher.

00:01:42.336 --> 00:01:52.384
Moses wrote for us that if a man's brother dies and leaves a wife but leaves no child, the man must take the widow and raise up offspring for his brother.

00:01:51.904 --> 00:01:52.576
other.

00:01:52.768 --> 00:01:55.712
There were seven brothers. The first took a wife.

00:01:55.584 --> 00:02:00.288
And when he died, left no offspring, and the second took her.

00:02:00.128 --> 00:02:08.544
And died, leaving no offspring, and the third likewise, and the seven left no offspring. Last of all, the woman also died.

00:02:09.024 --> 00:02:12.288
In the resurrection, when they rise again,

00:02:12.352 --> 00:02:15.232
Whose wife will she be?

00:02:15.392 --> 00:02:17.760
For the seven have had her.

00:02:17.792 --> 00:02:19.168
As wife.

00:02:20.096 --> 00:02:21.920
Jesus said to them,

00:02:21.888 --> 00:02:27.584
Is this not the reason you are wrong, because you know neither the scriptures?

00:02:27.456 --> 00:02:29.504
"nor the power of god."

00:02:29.792 --> 00:02:36.992
For when they rise from the dead, they neither marry nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.

00:02:37.216 --> 00:02:44.192
And as for the dead being raised, have you not read in the book of Moses, in the passage about the bush?

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:46.432
Have God spoke to him, saying,

00:02:46.208 --> 00:02:51.808
I am the God of Abraham and the God of Isaac and the God of Jacob.

00:02:52.384 --> 00:02:54.464
He is not God of the dead,

00:02:54.432 --> 00:02:56.000
But of the living,

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:57.024
You

00:02:56.960 --> 00:02:58.464
Are quite wrong.

00:03:00.032 --> 00:03:04.192
So Jesus defends the truth in two encounters.

00:03:04.160 --> 00:03:12.896
The Pharisees and Herodians seek to trap him about taxes and loyalty to God. The Sadducees seek to make him trust.

00:03:12.832 --> 00:03:17.056
Make his trust in God's word concerning the resurrection.

00:03:16.768 --> 00:03:18.240
Look foolish.

00:03:18.304 --> 00:03:20.192
Let's take them in turn.

00:03:20.448 --> 00:03:30.496
And that's actually our first lesson. Never be surprised when people who otherwise disagree and oppose each other stand together to oppose Jesus.

00:03:30.016 --> 00:03:36.096
And that's because Jesus is polarizing. You are either with him or against him.

00:03:35.968 --> 00:03:38.048
Those who are against him.

00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:41.376
See that he's the biggest threat to them.

00:03:41.088 --> 00:03:47.328
So they'll conspire against him and his church, try to make God's word look foolish.

00:03:47.424 --> 00:03:48.288
yet.

00:03:48.288 --> 00:03:49.568
So often,

00:03:49.536 --> 00:03:52.000
They've never even read his word.

00:03:53.152 --> 00:03:54.080
Now,

00:03:53.888 --> 00:03:56.864
Notice the subtlety of the first question.

00:03:56.608 --> 00:04:01.216
Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar or not? Should we pay them?

00:04:01.056 --> 00:04:02.464
Or should we not?

00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:07.872
Now, if he had said, pay them, the Pharisees would have accused him before the priests.

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:11.584
For supporting the Roman subjection of the Jews.

00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:20.320
If he said, don't pay them, the Herodians would have accused him before Pilate of rebellion and sedition.

00:04:20.576 --> 00:04:24.128
So the trap was crafty, like Satan himself.

00:04:24.544 --> 00:04:29.024
then what are the rights of our governors and the state?

00:04:28.864 --> 00:04:36.928
And the rights of God and his church. it raises that question, and many Christians have struggled to navigate those waters. What?

00:04:36.704 --> 00:04:42.240
If the state is at odds with the church, what if our governors are at odds with God?

00:04:42.688 --> 00:04:44.000
Jesus

00:04:43.712 --> 00:04:46.080
Impresses us with his wisdom.

00:04:46.272 --> 00:04:48.960
He knew the mystery, the hypocrisy,

00:04:48.864 --> 00:04:50.432
Of his enemies.

00:04:50.272 --> 00:04:53.632
He knew they used the common coin of the realm,

00:04:53.568 --> 00:04:54.944
so he says.

00:04:54.848 --> 00:04:56.096
Bring me one.

00:04:56.320 --> 00:04:57.760
Then he asks,

00:04:57.504 --> 00:04:59.200
whose face is on it.

00:04:59.232 --> 00:05:01.152
They answered Caesar's.

00:05:00.992 --> 00:05:07.520
By their own words, they acknowledge they have some duty to the governing authority. They use its money.

00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:17.728
So he says, render to Caesar the things that are Caesar's, and to God the things that are God's. You have obligations, he says, it matters temporal, and.

00:05:17.248 --> 00:05:18.752
And spiritual.

00:05:18.464 --> 00:05:28.512
Pay taxes, in temporal things, give honor to God, in spiritual things. In short, says J. C. Ryle, he bids the proud Pharisee.

00:05:28.032 --> 00:05:31.680
See, not to refuse his dues to Caesar, but

00:05:31.776 --> 00:05:37.248
And the worldly Herodian, not to refuse his dues to God.

00:05:37.344 --> 00:05:39.680
As the Apostle Paul says:

00:05:39.552 --> 00:05:41.888
In Romans 13:7,

00:05:41.632 --> 00:05:46.240
Pay to all what is owed to them, taxes to whom taxes are owed.

00:05:46.080 --> 00:05:48.672
Revenue to whom revenue is owed.

00:05:48.416 --> 00:05:49.792
respect,

00:05:49.600 --> 00:05:53.984
To whom respect is owed, honour to whom honour is owed.

00:05:54.016 --> 00:05:57.184
Or as the apostle Peter says in first Peter two.

00:05:56.992 --> 00:05:59.488
Live as people who are free

00:05:59.552 --> 00:06:03.008
Not using your freedom as a cover-up for evil

00:06:02.848 --> 00:06:05.088
But living the servants of God.

00:06:05.216 --> 00:06:06.816
Honor everyone.

00:06:06.784 --> 00:06:08.320
Love the brotherhood.

00:06:08.480 --> 00:06:09.952
Fear God,

00:06:10.240 --> 00:06:11.808
Honor the Emperor.

00:06:12.448 --> 00:06:13.952
We are to submit

00:06:14.112 --> 00:06:15.424
To God,

00:06:15.328 --> 00:06:21.728
By obeying our earthly governors, unless they command what he forbids, or forbid what he commands.

00:06:21.984 --> 00:06:30.528
Today amidst the coronavirus, I'm thankful for the wisdom of our Arkansas governor in never commanding the closing of churches, even.

00:06:30.368 --> 00:06:33.792
While encouraging physical distancing in every place.

00:06:33.728 --> 00:06:34.656
Keep,

00:06:34.432 --> 00:06:39.424
Praying friends for our governor and for our church's elders, that we would all.

00:06:39.456 --> 00:06:40.672
Honor God.

00:06:41.728 --> 00:06:48.768
Now, in the second confrontation with the Sadducees, they ask him whom a widow will be married to in heaven.

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:58.752
If she has been married multiple times, they try to make the Old Testament hope of resurrection seem ridiculous. This is because, as Jesus says, they are ignorant.

00:06:58.464 --> 00:07:00.288
and don't believe in God.

00:06:59.936 --> 00:07:03.872
"'Jesus said to them, "'Is this not the reason you are wrong?'

00:07:03.552 --> 00:07:07.264
Because you know neither the scriptures nor the power of God.

00:07:07.712 --> 00:07:12.288
Let us determine, friends, to not be like them.

00:07:12.448 --> 00:07:17.312
How sad it is to be ignorant of the Bible, yet rail against it.

00:07:17.344 --> 00:07:18.944
And how harmful!

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:23.552
ignorance leaves us without hope when there is so much to be hopeful for.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:33.344
The Sadducees didn't believe in the resurrection or the power of God, but Jesus tells them they are wrong, and he proves it in two ways. First, he says.

00:07:33.088 --> 00:07:39.136
When we rise from the dead, we neither marry nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.

00:07:39.616 --> 00:07:41.664
Life in heaven.

00:07:41.696 --> 00:07:43.968
will be different than on earth.

00:07:43.904 --> 00:07:46.528
Though our body will rise from the dead,

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:53.920
We shall hunger no more, and thirst no more. There will be no more death or mourning or crying or pain.

00:07:53.664 --> 00:07:58.560
And in heaven, we will all be brothers and sisters in the household of God.

00:07:58.560 --> 00:08:02.912
But we will not have marriage binding one man to one woman that

00:08:02.720 --> 00:08:04.256
Doesn't mean

00:08:04.448 --> 00:08:14.496
Husbands and wives and families here can't spend time together or love one another. There, of course, will love. Heaven is a reunion.

00:08:14.016 --> 00:08:18.976
In a world of love in ways you and I haven't yet begun to enjoy.

00:08:19.872 --> 00:08:24.224
But the marriage of heaven is between Jesus and his bride.

00:08:24.256 --> 00:08:25.600
The church.

00:08:26.336 --> 00:08:31.168
Secondly, Jesus says you're wrong because God is the God of the living.

00:08:31.040 --> 00:08:41.088
And the Bible says he's the God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob. Not that he was the God of them as if they are dead, but that he is the God of them because they live with.

00:08:40.608 --> 00:08:41.856
Live with him.

00:08:41.504 --> 00:08:44.160
His power to give life,

00:08:44.032 --> 00:08:45.568
is our hope.

00:08:46.144 --> 00:08:49.600
if in christ we have hope in this life only.

00:08:49.728 --> 00:08:53.184
We are, of all people, most to be pitied.

00:08:53.152 --> 00:08:58.080
but in fact christ has been raised from the dead and the dead in christ.

00:08:58.048 --> 00:08:59.680
Shall rise.

00:08:59.616 --> 00:09:00.896
Therefore,

00:09:00.896 --> 00:09:03.360
My beloved brothers and sisters

00:09:03.424 --> 00:09:05.056
Be steadfast.

00:09:05.056 --> 00:09:06.400
Immovable.

00:09:06.496 --> 00:09:10.912
Always abounding in the work of the Lord, knowing that in the Lord.

00:09:10.944 --> 00:09:13.664
Your labor is not

00:09:13.536 --> 00:09:14.912
In vain.

00:09:15.328 --> 00:09:16.608
Let's pray together.

00:09:17.216 --> 00:09:27.264
Our Heavenly Father, the God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, we praise you for Jesus, whom you raised from the dead and exalted over every name.

00:09:26.784 --> 00:09:29.600
We bow and confess that he is faithful.

00:09:29.408 --> 00:09:32.640
King of kings and Lord of lords.

00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:33.760
Help us.

00:09:33.664 --> 00:09:35.392
To hope in him.

00:09:35.808 --> 00:09:37.024
big man

00:09:37.440 --> 00:09:39.232
Well, thank you for listening.

00:09:38.976 --> 00:09:40.960
And I hope you'll join me next time.
